sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant Django as Django Backend
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)

    Note over Browser,IdP: Pure Django SAML — SP-initiated, Django acts as SAML Service Provider

    Browser->>Django: GET /api/auth/discovery?email=user@example.com
    Note over Django: Look up IdP by email domain<br/>Build SAML AuthnRequest via pysaml2<br/>Sign RelayState={reqid, next}
    Django-->>Browser: 302 Location: https://login.microsoftonline.com/...?SAMLRequest=...&RelayState=...

    Browser->>IdP: GET (SAMLRequest redirect)
    Note over IdP: User enters credentials<br/>IdP validates identity
    IdP-->>Browser: HTML form auto-posting SAMLResponse

    Browser->>Django: POST /api/auth/saml/acs/<br/>SAMLResponse=...&RelayState=...
    Note over Django: Validate assertion (signature + expiry)<br/>Extract email claim<br/>Create or find auth_user (DB internal)<br/>Issue DRF Token (DB internal)
    Django-->>Browser: 302 Location: /dashboard/#django_token=abc123&email=user@example.com

    Note over Browser: Login complete — DRF token stored locally
